      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver must demonstrate correct numerical implementation via benchmark problems with known analytical solutions.",
      "rationale": "The CFD solver was verified against the lid-driven cavity benchmark and the Hagen-Poiseuille pipe flow solution. Velocity profiles matched analytical solutions within 0.5% at the mesh resolution used for production simulations. Code verification is documented in the solver qualification report."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) must be below 5% for primary quantities of interest at the mesh resolution used in production simulations.",
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh refinement study was conducted on the FDA centrifugal pump geometry. Richardson extrapolation yielded GCI values of 1.8% for NIH and 2.1% for peak wall shear stress between medium and fine meshes, both below the 5% threshold. The medium mesh (4.8M cells) was adopted for production runs. Detailed results are discussed in the grid independence study activity narrative and summarized in the validation result reports."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
