      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions must be documented with sufficient detail to allow replication and must correspond to the intended operating envelope of the CPB device.",
      "rationale": "In-vitro hemolysis experiments were conducted using bovine blood at 37°C with hematocrit 35±2%. Flow rates and rotational speeds were controlled within ±1% of target values. Test conditions span the full clinical operating envelope (3–6 L/min, 2500–3500 RPM) as specified in the COU."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
