      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "CFD-predicted NIH values must agree with experimental measurements within 15% relative error across all validation operating points.",
      "rationale": "Predicted NIH values were compared to experimental measurements at five operating conditions. Maximum relative error was 8.3%; mean relative error was 5.1%. All comparisons satisfied the 15% acceptance criterion. Results are documented in ValidationResult hemolysis-bench-comparison-001."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The quantities of interest used in validation (NIH, RH) must be directly relevant to the clinical hemolysis decision for the CPB COU.",
      "rationale": "NIH and RH are the standard metrics for regulatory hemolysis assessment per ASTM F1841. Both quantities directly characterize the hemolytic potential relevant to the clinical decision. The RH < 1 acceptance criterion is established in FDA guidance for predicate device comparisons."
    },
    {
